Reflection:
The IDS Fundamentals room taught me how intrusion detection systems work alongside firewalls: 
firewalls block traffic, while IDS monitors and alerts without blocking. 
I learned Snort's basics, reviewed default rules, and wrote custom Snort rules from scratch. 
This reinforced that IDS is about detection and notification, not prevention—critical for layered security and SOC work.
